          "right": "two days later"
        },
        {
          "id": "p4",
          "left": "l'année précédente",
          "right": "the previous year"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "ex-ro-1",
      "type": "reorder",
      "skill": "writing",
      "prompt": "Put the words in order: \"I had told him so.\"",
      "tokens": [
        {
          "id": "t1",
          "text": "Je"
        },
        {
          "id": "t2",
          "text": "le"
        },
        {
          "id": "t3",
          "text": "lui"
        },
        {
          "id": "t4",
          "text": "avais"
        },
        {
          "id": "t5",
          "text": "bien"
        },
        {
          "id": "t6",
          "text": "dit"
        }
      ],
      "correctOrder": [
        "t1",
        "t2",
        "t3",
        "t4",
        "t5",
        "t6"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "ex-li-1",
      "type": "listen",
      "skill": "listening",
      "prompt": "Listen to the start of the story. What happened, in what order?",
      "audio": "audio/b1.2/unit-06-pronouns-narration/listen-1.mp3",
      "transcript": "La veille du procès, son avocate lui avait promis la victoire ; le lendemain, ils ont pourtant perdu.",
      "options": [
        {
          "id": "a",
          "text": "The lawyer promised victory the day before the trial — but they lost the day after"
        },
        {
          "id": "b",
          "text": "They won the trial thanks to the lawyer's promise"
        },
        {
          "id": "c",
          "text": "The trial was postponed by two days"
        }
      ],
      "correct": [
        "a"
      ],
      "explanation": "la veille (promise) → le lendemain (loss, despite the promise — pourtant!)."
    },
    {
      "id": "ex-rd-1",
      "type": "read",
      "skill": "reading",
      "prompt": "Read this extract from a history programme and answer both questions.",
      "passageFr": "Le procès de la reine a duré deux jours. La veille, ses avocats avaient enfin été désignés. Le lendemain de la condamnation, elle a été exécutée. Quelques années plus tard, ses accusateurs ont connu le même destin — l'Histoire le leur a fait payer.",
      "passageEn": "The queen's trial lasted two days. The day before, her lawyers had finally been appointed. The day after the sentencing, she was executed. A few years later, her accusers met the same fate — History made them pay for it.",
      "questions": [
        {
          "id": "q1",
          "prompt": "When were the queen's lawyers appointed?",
          "options": [
            {
              "id": "a",
              "text": "The day before the trial"
            },
            {
              "id": "b",
              "text": "The day after the sentencing"
            },
            {
              "id": "c",
              "text": "A few years later"
            }
          ],
          "correct": [
            "a"
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "q2",
          "prompt": "What happened to the accusers a few years later?",
          "options": [
            {
              "id": "a",
              "text": "They met the same fate"
            },
            {
              "id": "b",
              "text": "They were pardoned"
            },
            {
              "id": "c",
              "text": "They left the country"
            }
          ],
          "correct": [
            "a"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "ex-mc-4",
      "type": "multiple-choice",
      "skill": "writing",
      "prompt": "An or année? « Ils ont vécu là pendant trois ___. »",
      "options": [
        {
          "id": "a",
          "text": "ans"
        },
        {
          "id": "b",
          "text": "années"
        },
        {
          "id": "c",
          "text": "an"
        }
      ],
      "correct": [
        "a"
      ],
      "explanation": "Exact count → ans (trois ans). Année is for imprecise amounts or with adjectives (quelques années, l'année suivante)."
    },
